Nigerian gospel music super star, Frank Edwards has donated the sum of N250,000 for the upkeep of an abandoned 2-year old child of a mentally challenged woman in Agbani area of Enugu state.
Recall that a Nigerian man identified as Benkingsley Nwashara came to the aid of the abandoned 2-year-old child who found the baby by the roadside, and had taken the kid home on the instruction of the DPO of the police station where his discovery was reported
The kindhearted man stated that the baby was heavily battered by the rainfall where she was found and that market women watched the kid without rendering help.
On Wednesday, June 15, Benkingsley had shared photos on Twitter of a little girl he had picked up around Agbani, Enugu state.
READ ALSO: Parents of children who died in abandoned vehicle open up
He said the child belongs to a mentally challenged woman who stays at Eke Agbani, Enugu. Upon picking her up, Benkingsley said he took her to the police station and was told to take her home and come the next day.
In a subsequent tweet, Benkingsley lamented how the market women in the area the kid was picked from abandoned her.
According to him, the baby was battered by the heavy downpour. “…This baby has suffered tremendously. She sat at that same spot while all the rain that fell yesterday battered her.
He heaved a sigh of relief that the baby was gradually getting her health back after a treatment period at the hospital that lasted 15 hours.
He wrote: “…Please we need advice on the proper diet to feed her for now. I don’t know how to take care of babies.”
Frank Edwards who took to his twitter handle said, “Kindly let me know if you need anything to get the baby in a perfect state. Anything at all.
“I don’t know what you need to get the baby the necessary medical checkups and clothing but I just sent this. Let me know if any more is needed.

